  <md:abstract>By the end of this section, you will be able to:
<list>
<item>Explain how the kidneys serve as the main osmoregulatory organs in mammalian systems</item>
<item>Describe the structure of the kidneys and the functions of the parts of the kidney</item>
<item>Describe how the nephron is the functional unit of the kidney and explain how it actively filters blood and generates urine</item>
<item>Detail the three steps in the formation of urine: glomerular filtration, tubular reabsorption, and tubular secretion</item>
</list></md:abstract>
